{"id": "samsung_elec-2026-04-29-012", "date": "2026-04-29", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Wed"}, "entities": {"companies": ["samsung_elec", "boe"], "customers": ["samsung_elec"], "suppliers": ["boe"]}, "topics": ["oled_penetration"], "sentiment": {"label": "negative", "score": -0.5, "keywords": ["[否定]increase"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.9, "reasons": ["多公司提及", "供應鏈上下游同時提及"]}, "title": "BOE resumes production of iPhone 17 AMOLEDs after it regained approval from Apple", "content": "<p>In early 2026 it was reported that <a href=\"https://www.oled-info.com/boe-halted-some-its-iphone-amoled-production-its-b11-fab-december-it-suffers\">BOE has been suffering from disruptions at its B11 AMOLED production line</a>, which is where BOE produces smartphone AMOLED displays for Apple's iPhones. The production line started having quality issues at some of the processes, and BOE halted production already in November 2025. Apple had to increase its orders from Samsung Display.</p><p><a hr", "sources": [{"name": "oled_info", "url": "https://www.oled-info.com/boe-resumes-production-iphone-17-amoleds-after-it-regained-approval-apple", "type": "rss"}]}
